newsitem.title: NETHERLANDS: Higher USDA figures keep European feeds tradeless.
newsitem.headline: Higher USDA figures keep European feeds tradeless.

text.p: Higher than expected USDA U.S. soybean crop figures kept the European meals and feeds market tradesless today, market sources said.

"This morning nobody wanted to do business ahead of the USDA crop data and after the figures were released everybody decided to wait and see how far Chicago soycomplex futures would drop before doing anything again. So maybe we'll see some action tomorrow," one broker said.
USDA set the U.S. 1996 soybean crop at 2.403 bln bushels against 2,346 a month ago and 2,177 in 1995. After around 90 minutes of trade Chicago soymeal futures were $1.6 to $4.5 down.
